comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T16:52:53.882Z",codex-derived-context-20260721,"Duplicate check (all statuses, 2026-07-21): exact searches for GH-628, GH-629, and GH-630 returned no items. Reuses parent pm-92if and relates historical class owners pm-zt1c (spread), pm-fmjy (duplication), and pm-m8yl (unsafe optional chaining) instead of reopening completed work."
  "2026-07-21T18:22:50.939Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-21: reproduce and remediate the three grouped GitHub analyzer reports in the same broad SDK/quality PR; direct tracker-link comments were added to GH-628, GH-629, and GH-630."
  "2026-07-21T19:26:19.236Z",codex-root,"Implementation evidence: GH-628 replaces the unnecessary graph result spread with direct cache annotation; GH-629 centralizes project-context field keys in ITEM_PROJECT_CONTEXT_KEYS and reuses them in structured mutations; GH-630 adds an explicit committed-result guard before structuredContent access. GitHub issues #628/#629/#630 each received a direct pm-aw59hb link. Typecheck, strict static quality, 100% coverage, and 205 focused SDK/graph/mutation tests pass."
  "2026-07-21T19:38:46.493Z",codex-root,"Hosted static follow-up: CI exposed four ESLint-only findings not included in the earlier composite command. Removed redundant copy warning initializers, documented the two intentional best-effort cache catches, and pruned the now-obsolete no-useless-assignment suppression. Exact hosted command parity now passes locally: pnpm lint (ESLint, zero jscpd clones, CodeFactor/static/docstrings/package boundary/token budget) plus focused copy/index tests 9/9."
  "2026-07-21T19:46:07.947Z",codex-root,"Hosted CI finding: coverage shard 4/4 caught release-contract drift after the obsolete ESLint suppression was pruned. The live suppression count is 150 while MAX_ESLINT_SUPPRESSIONS and package-script assertions remained 151. Tightening the pinned baseline to 150 across the gate, package script, and contract tests before the next push."
  "2026-07-21T19:48:53.685Z",codex-root,"Hosted CI fix verified locally: release automation/readiness/static-quality contracts pass 115/115, pnpm lint passes with zero clones and strict static/docstring/package/token gates, and pnpm typecheck passes. The suppression budget is now pinned to the exact live baseline of 150 so future growth cannot hide behind the stale allowance."
  "2026-07-21T20:06:13.455Z",codex-root,"PR #636 exact-head review evidence at e0ae27f0: all hosted checks pass, including merged 100% coverage, static quality, CodeQL, Semgrep, Trivy, CodeFactor, DeepScan, Windows, docs, smokes, and CodSpeed. All six CodeRabbit threads were individually reacted to and replied to; valid findings are fixed and every thread is resolved. Gemini is sunset, Sourcery and CodeRabbit reported quota/rate limits after completion, and Greptile produced no review artifact despite repeated triggers. PR #636 declares Closes #628/#629/#630 so GitHub will close all three on merge."
